#Anova to check if the difference between cruises MLD

MLD <- read_xlsx("MLD.xlsx")

# Compute the analysis of variance cruise
res.aov <- aov(MLD  ~ Cruise, data = MLD)
# Summary of the analysis
summary(res.aov)
##             Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value   Pr(>F)    
## Cruise       1   3948    3948   13.18 0.000616 ***
## Residuals   56  16781     300                     
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
# 1. Homogeneity of variances
plot(res.aov, 1)

leveneTest(MLD  ~ Cruise, data = MLD)
## Warning in leveneTest.default(y = y, group = group, ...): group coerced to
## factor.
## Levene's Test for Homogeneity of Variance (center = median)
##       Df F value Pr(>F)
## group  1  0.2851 0.5955
##       56
#From the output above we can see that the p-value is not less than the significance level of 0.05. This means that there is no evidence to suggest that the variance across groups is statistically significantly different. Therefore, we can assume the homogeneity of variances in the different treatment groups.
